{"overview":"A compact waltz in B major with a graceful ternary-like layout, this piece is harmonically straightforward yet distinguished by its smooth diatonic excursion to E major (IV) and the sustained pedal tones that lend each section a quietly suspended, lyrical quality. Its most distinctive feature is the interplay between a rocking bass pedal in the opening theme and the floating middle-voice F-sharp pedal of the B section, creating two contrasting textural identities within a single intimate mood.","cross_piece_tags":["ternary","pedal_point","lyrical","meditative","intimate","circle_of_fifths","arpeggiated_bass"]}
